      "question": "Evaluate the following expression: $\\frac{\\cos 58^\\circ}{\\sin 32^\\circ} + \\frac{\\sin 22^\\circ}{\\cos 68^\\circ} - \\frac{\\cos 38^\\circ \\csc 52^\\circ}{\\tan 18^\\circ \\tan 35^\\circ \\tan 60^\\circ \\tan 72^\\circ \\tan 55^\\circ}$.",
      "answer": "1 - \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Use complementary angle relations $\\cos(90^\\circ - \\theta) = \\sin \\theta$ and $\\tan(90^\\circ - \\theta) = \\cot \\theta$.",
          "Simplify the individual terms in the expression.",
          "Substitute the value of $\\tan 60^\\circ = \\sqrt{3}$ and simplify the final result."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\frac{\\cos(90^\\circ-32^\\circ)}{\\sin 32^\\circ} + \\frac{\\sin(90^\\circ-68^\\circ)}{\\cos 68^\\circ} - \\frac{\\cos 38^\\circ \\cdot (1/\\sin 52^\\circ)}{\\tan 18^\\circ \\tan 35^\\circ \\sqrt{3} \\cot 18^\\circ \\cot 35^\\circ} \\\\ = \\frac{\\sin 32^\\circ}{\\sin 32^\\circ} + \\frac{\\cos 68^\\circ}{\\cos 68^\\circ} - \\frac{\\cos 38^\\circ / \\cos 38^\\circ}{\\sqrt{3}} \\\\ = 1 + 1 - \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}} = 2 - \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}"
      },
